{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018ucP3aA3RvoRBVk28jQQsR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{\n     2→  \"project\": \"VuePoint — Visual Annotation \\u0026 AI Agent Feedback Tool for Vue 3\",\n     3→  \"description\": \"VuePoint is an internal JumpCloud tool that adds a visual annotation toolbar to live Vue 3 applications. Engineers, designers, and PMs can point at UI elements and generate structured, machine-readable feedback (CSS selectors, Vue component hierarchies, SFC file paths) that AI coding agents can act on directly. Instead of describing \\\"the blue button on the left,\\\" users hand an agent a precise selector and component chain, cutting feedback loops from minutes to seconds.\",\n     4→  \"userStories\": [\n     5→    {\n     6→      \"id\": \"US-001\",\n     7→      \"title\": \"Scaffold monorepo directory structure\",\n     8→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need the project organized as a pnpm monorepo so that cross-package imports resolve and the project can be built, tested, and published.\",\n     9→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    10→        \"Directory structure created: packages/core/, packages/vue/, packages/bridge/, packages/mcp/, packages/api/, packages/nuxt/, playground/\",\n    11→        \"Existing 11 source files moved to their correct package locations per architecture spec\",\n    12→        \"Root package.json with pnpm workspaces configuration\",\n    13→        \"Per-package package.json with correct name, exports, dependencies, and peerDependencies\",\n    14→        \"Root tsconfig.json and per-package tsconfig.json with project references\",\n    15→        \"pnpm install succeeds without errors\",\n    16→        \"Cross-package imports (@vuepoint/core from @vuepoint/vue) resolve correctly in TypeScript\"\n    17→      ],\n    18→      \"priority\": 1,\n    19→      \"passes\": false\n    20→    },\n    21→    {\n    22→      \"id\": \"US-002\",\n    23→      \"title\": \"Build system with Vite\",\n    24→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need each package to build via Vite so that the project produces consumable ESM + CJS output.\",\n    25→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    26→        \"vite.config.ts in each publishable package (core, vue, mcp, api)\",\n    27→        \"pnpm build from root builds all packages in dependency order\",\n    28→        \"@vuepoint/core outputs ESM + CJS with TypeScript declarations\",\n    29→        \"@vuepoint/vue outputs ESM + CJS with TypeScript declarations and .vue SFC compilation\",\n    30→        \"@vuepoint/mcp outputs a runnable Node.js entry point\",\n    31→        \"@vuepoint/api outputs a runnable Node.js entry point\",\n    32→        \"pnpm typecheck passes across all packages\"\n    33→      ],\n    34→      \"priority\": 1,\n    35→      \"passes\": false\n    36→    },\n    37→    {\n    38→      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n    39→      \"title\": \"Vue component hierarchy resolution\",\n    40→      \"description\": \"As a developer using an AI agent, I want annotations to include the full Vue component chain and SFC file path so the agent can navigate directly to the source file.\",\n    41→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    42→        \"useVueInspector.ts walks __vueParentComponent from clicked element to app root\",\n    43→        \"Component names resolved from __name, name, or __file fallback\",\n    44→        \"SFC file path extracted from component.type.__file and normalized (strips absolute prefix)\",\n    45→        \"Vue built-in components (Transition, KeepAlive, etc.) filtered out\",\n    46→        \"Chain returned in root-to-leaf order: \\u003cApp\\u003e -\\u003e \\u003cPageView\\u003e -\\u003e \\u003cTargetComponent\\u003e\",\n    47→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    48→      ],\n    49→      \"priority\": 1,\n    50→      \"passes\": false\n    51→    },\n    52→    {\n    53→      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n    54→      \"title\": \"CSS selector generation\",\n    55→      \"description\": \"As a developer using an AI agent, I want each annotation to include a unique CSS selector so the agent can grep for or target the exact element.\",\n    56→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    57→        \"generateSelector() produces a unique CSS path from root to target element\",\n    58→        \"Prioritizes: #id \\u003e [data-testid] \\u003e tag + classes \\u003e :nth-child()\",\n    59→        \"Max depth of 8 to keep selectors readable\",\n    60→        \"describeElement() returns a human-readable summary (tag, classes, text content)\",\n    61→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    62→      ],\n    63→      \"priority\": 1,\n    64→      \"passes\": false\n    65→    },\n    66→    {\n    67→      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n    68→      \"title\": \"Markdown output formatter\",\n    69→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want annotations formatted as structured Markdown so I can paste them into any AI agent chat.\",\n    70→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    71→        \"formatAnnotation() outputs Markdown with: Element, Selector, Component chain, SFC Path, Pinia Stores, Feedback, Expected, Actual, Route\",\n    72→        \"formatAnnotationBatch() formats multiple annotations with numbered headers\",\n    73→        \"Optional fields (Expected, Actual, Pinia Stores) omitted when empty\",\n    74→        \"Output is greppable and machine-parseable\",\n    75→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    76→      ],\n    77→      \"priority\": 1,\n    78→      \"passes\": false\n    79→    },\n    80→    {\n    81→      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n    82→      \"title\": \"PrimeVue component filtering\",\n    83→      \"description\": \"As a developer using PrimeVue, I want library-internal components filtered from the hierarchy so annotations show only my own components.\",\n    84→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    85→        \"Default filter list covers 35+ PrimeVue internal components (PButton, PDialog, etc.)\",\n    86→        \"Vue built-in components (Transition, KeepAlive, Suspense, etc.) always filtered\",\n    87→        \"buildFilter() accepts: false (no filtering), string[] (custom list), or undefined (defaults)\",\n    88→        \"Filter is configurable via VuePointOptions.filterComponents\",\n    89→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n    90→      ],\n    91→      \"priority\": 1,\n    92→      \"passes\": false\n    93→    },\n    94→    {\n    95→      \"id\": \"US-007\",\n    96→      \"title\": \"Annotation state management\",\n    97→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a reactive annotation store so the toolbar, markers, and integrations all share the same state.\",\n    98→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n    99→        \"useAnnotations() composable provides reactive annotations array and pending/resolved computed filters\",\n   100→        \"CRUD operations: create, update, acknowledge, resolve, dismiss, remove, clear\",\n   101→        \"Each annotation gets a unique ID and timestamp on creation\",\n   102→        \"Status lifecycle: pending -\\u003e acknowledged -\\u003e resolved | dismissed\",\n   103→        \"Store is framework-agnostic (plain Vue ref/computed, not Pinia)\",\n   104→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   105→      ],\n   106→      \"priority\": 1,\n   107→      \"passes\": false\n   108→    },\n   109→    {\n   110→      \"id\": \"US-008\",\n   111→      \"title\": \"Vue plugin entry with production guard\",\n   112→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want to install VuePoint with app.use(VuePoint) and have it auto-disable in production.\",\n   113→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   114→        \"app.use(VuePoint) installs the toolbar with zero config\",\n   115→        \"app.use(VuePoint, { ...options }) accepts full VuePointOptions\",\n   116→        \"Production guard: disabled when NODE_ENV === 'production' or import.meta.env.PROD === true\",\n   117→        \"Toolbar rendered in an isolated Vue app instance (separate from host app — does not appear in __vueParentComponent chain)\",\n   118→        \"Keyboard shortcut parsed and registered (default: Ctrl+Shift+A)\",\n   119→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   120→      ],\n   121→      \"priority\": 1,\n   122→      \"passes\": false\n   123→    },\n   124→    {\n   125→      \"id\": \"US-009\",\n   126→      \"title\": \"Core toolbar — click-to-annotate flow\",\n   127→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to click any element in my app and create an annotation with structured feedback.\",\n   128→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   129→        \"FAB button (collapsed by default) expands toolbar on click\",\n   130→        \"Activating \\\"annotate mode\\\" changes cursor and highlights elements on hover\",\n   131→        \"Clicking an element captures: selector, component chain, SFC path, bounding rect\",\n   132→        \"Feedback modal appears with text input for user's description\",\n   133→        \"Submitting creates an annotation in the store\",\n   134→        \"Annotation marker (numbered badge) placed at the annotated element's position\",\n   135→        \"\\\"Copy All\\\" button generates Markdown output to clipboard\",\n   136→        \"Keyboard shortcut toggles toolbar visibility\",\n   137→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   138→      ],\n   139→      \"priority\": 1,\n   140→      \"passes\": false\n   141→    },\n   142→    {\n   143→      \"id\": \"US-010\",\n   144→      \"title\": \"Create AnnotationMarker component\",\n   145→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to see numbered badges on annotated elements so I can visually track which elements have feedback.\",\n   146→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   147→        \"AnnotationMarker.vue renders a positioned numbered badge at each annotation's bounding rect\",\n   148→        \"Badge updates position on scroll and resize\",\n   149→        \"Clicking a badge selects that annotation in the panel\",\n   150→        \"Badge color reflects annotation status (pending = blue, acknowledged = orange, resolved = green)\",\n   151→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   152→      ],\n   153→      \"priority\": 1,\n   154→      \"passes\": false\n   155→    },\n   156→    {\n   157→      \"id\": \"US-011\",\n   158→      \"title\": \"Create AnnotationPanel component\",\n   159→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want a panel listing all annotations so I can review, edit, and manage them.\",\n   160→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   161→        \"AnnotationPanel.vue renders a scrollable list of all annotations\",\n   162→        \"Each item shows: number, element description, feedback text, status badge\",\n   163→        \"Delete button removes an annotation\",\n   164→        \"Clicking an item scrolls the page to the annotated element\",\n   165→        \"Empty state message when no annotations exist\",\n   166→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   167→      ],\n   168→      \"priority\": 1,\n   169→      \"passes\": false\n   170→    },\n   171→    {\n   172→      \"id\": \"US-012\",\n   173→      \"title\": \"Expected/Actual fields in feedback form\",\n   174→      \"description\": \"As a user reporting a bug, I want to specify what I expected and what actually happened, so the AI agent has clear context.\",\n   175→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   176→        \"Feedback modal includes optional \\\"Expected behavior\\\" and \\\"Actual behavior\\\" text fields\",\n   177→        \"Fields are collapsible (hidden by default, expand on click)\",\n   178→        \"Values saved to annotation's expected and actual fields\",\n   179→        \"Included in Markdown output when present\",\n   180→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   181→      ],\n   182→      \"priority\": 2,\n   183→      \"passes\": false\n   184→    },\n   185→    {\n   186→      \"id\": \"US-013\",\n   187→      \"title\": \"Dark/light mode toggle\",\n   188→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want the toolbar to support dark and light themes so it matches my app's appearance.\",\n   189→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   190→        \"Toggle switch in toolbar header\",\n   191→        \"All toolbar components (FAB, panel, markers, modal) respect the theme\",\n   192→        \"Default theme auto-detected from prefers-color-scheme media query\",\n   193→        \"Theme preference persisted in localStorage\",\n   194→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   195→      ],\n   196→      \"priority\": 2,\n   197→      \"passes\": false\n   198→    },\n   199→    {\n   200→      \"id\": \"US-014\",\n   201→      \"title\": \"Playground development app\",\n   202→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I need a test app to develop and demo VuePoint in a realistic Vue 3 + PrimeVue environment.\",\n   203→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   204→        \"playground/ directory with a Vue 3 + Vite app\",\n   205→        \"PrimeVue installed and configured with sample components (DataTable, Button, Dialog, etc.)\",\n   206→        \"VuePoint installed via workspace link (@vuepoint/vue)\",\n   207→        \"Pinia store with sample data (e.g., a users list)\",\n   208→        \"Multiple routes to test route context capture\",\n   209→        \"pnpm dev starts the playground with hot reload\",\n   210→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   211→      ],\n   212→      \"priority\": 2,\n   213→      \"passes\": false\n   214→    },\n   215→    {\n   216→      \"id\": \"US-015\",\n   217→      \"title\": \"Multi-select annotation (drag)\",\n   218→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to drag-select multiple elements at once so I can annotate a group of related elements in one action.\",\n   219→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   220→        \"Hold Shift + drag to draw a selection rectangle\",\n   221→        \"All elements intersecting the rectangle are captured as a single multi-element annotation\",\n   222→        \"Each element's selector and component info included in the annotation\",\n   223→        \"Visual feedback during drag (selection rectangle overlay)\",\n   224→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   225→      ],\n   226→      \"priority\": 3,\n   227→      \"passes\": false\n   228→    },\n   229→    {\n   230→      \"id\": \"US-016\",\n   231→      \"title\": \"Area selection annotation\",\n   232→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to select an arbitrary rectangular area of the page to annotate layout or spacing issues that don't map to a single element.\",\n   233→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   234→        \"Alt + drag to draw an area selection\",\n   235→        \"Area annotation captures: bounding rect coordinates, screenshot of area (Phase 2), elements within bounds\",\n   236→        \"Distinct visual marker for area annotations (dashed border vs. badge)\",\n   237→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   238→      ],\n   239→      \"priority\": 3,\n   240→      \"passes\": false\n   241→    },\n   242→    {\n   243→      \"id\": \"US-017\",\n   244→      \"title\": \"Text selection annotation\",\n   245→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to select text on the page and annotate it to flag copy issues, typos, or content feedback.\",\n   246→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   247→        \"Select text, then click \\\"Annotate Selection\\\" in toolbar (or right-click context)\",\n   248→        \"Annotation captures: selected text, containing element selector, component chain\",\n   249→        \"Text highlight marker persists on the page\",\n   250→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   251→      ],\n   252→      \"priority\": 3,\n   253→      \"passes\": false\n   254→    },\n   255→    {\n   256→      \"id\": \"US-018\",\n   257→      \"title\": \"Animation pause\",\n   258→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to pause all CSS animations and transitions so I can annotate elements that are in motion.\",\n   259→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   260→        \"\\\"Pause Animations\\\" toggle in toolbar\",\n   261→        \"Injects * { animation-play-state: paused !important; transition: none !important; } globally\",\n   262→        \"Removing toggle restores original animation state\",\n   263→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   264→      ],\n   265→      \"priority\": 3,\n   266→      \"passes\": false\n   267→    },\n   268→    {\n   269→      \"id\": \"US-019\",\n   270→      \"title\": \"Inline editing in annotation panel\",\n   271→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to edit annotation feedback directly in the panel without reopening a modal.\",\n   272→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   273→        \"Double-click feedback text in panel to switch to inline edit mode\",\n   274→        \"Save on blur or Enter; cancel on Escape\",\n   275→        \"Updated text reflected in Markdown output immediately\",\n   276→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   277→      ],\n   278→      \"priority\": 3,\n   279→      \"passes\": false\n   280→    },\n   281→    {\n   282→      \"id\": \"US-020\",\n   283→      \"title\": \"Agent question display in toolbar\",\n   284→      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to see and answer questions from AI agents directly in the toolbar when an agent calls vuepoint_ask.\",\n   285→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   286→        \"When MCP agent calls vuepoint_ask, question appears as a notification badge on the toolbar\",\n   287→        \"Opening toolbar shows the question with a text reply field\",\n   288→        \"User's reply sent back through the bridge to the MCP server\",\n   289→        \"Question/answer history visible in annotation panel\",\n   290→        \"Typecheck passes\"\n   291→      ],\n   292→      \"priority\": 3,\n   293→      \"passes\": false\n   294→    },\n   295→    {\n   296→      \"id\": \"US-021\",\n   297→      \"title\": \"Per-component Pinia store resolution\",\n   298→      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want annotations to show which Pinia stores a specific component accesses, not just all stores in the app.\",\n   299→      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n   300→        \"useVueInspector resolves which store